2 PAIR:{nl}
Two separate pairs of{nl}
same-number cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}3 OF A KIND:{nl}
Three cards of the{nl}
same number.{waitkey}{clearbox}STRAIGHT:{nl}
Five cards in a run{nl}
of numbers.{waitkey}{clearbox}FLUSH:{nl}
Five cards all of the{nl}
same suit.{waitkey}{clearbox}FULL HOUSE:{nl}
A 3 OF A KIND plus a{nl}
pair in the other two.{waitkey}{clearbox}4 OF A KIND:{nl}
Four cards of the{nl}
same number.{waitkey}{clearbox}STRAIGHT FLUSH:{nl}
A STRAIGHT all of the{nl}
same suit.{waitkey}{clearbox}5 OF A KIND:{nl}
A 4 OF A KIND with the{nl}
fifth card a JOKER.{waitkey}{clearbox}ROYAL FLUSH{nl}
A STRAIGHT FLUSH of{nl}
10-J-Q-K-A.{waitkey}{clearbox}[Notes on hands]{waitkey}{clearbox}- In this poker, 1 PAIR{nl}
 alone is not a hand.{waitkey}{clearbox}- STRAIGHT-type hands{nl}
 can't run from A down to 2.{waitkey}{clearbox}- The JOKER is a wild card{waitkey} and can stand in for any{nl}
 hand except 5 OF A KIND.{waitkey}{ret}

A Blackjack game played{nl}
one-on-one with the dealer.{waitkey}{clearbox}The computer acts as{nl}
the dealer.{waitkey}{clearbox}First, the player and dealer{nl}
are each dealt two cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}One of the dealer's two{nl}
cards is face down.{waitkey}{clearbox}Only when the dealer's face-up{nl}
card is an Ace{waitkey}can you take{nl}
INSURANCE.{waitkey}{clearbox}INSURANCE is covered{nl}
near the end of these{nl}
rules.{waitkey}{clearbox}First, compare the dealer's{nl}
card with your own and decide{nl}
whether to draw one more.{waitkey}{clearbox}To draw another, choose "HIT";{nl}
to stop, choose "STAND".{waitkey}{clearbox}So long as your total{nl}
stays under 21, you can{nl}
draw up to seven cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}Note: you STAND automatically{nl}
in the following cases.{waitkey}{clearbox}- When the first two cards{nl}
 dealt are a Blackjack.{waitkey}{clearbox}- When a card from the third{nl}
 on brings your total to 21.{waitkey}{clearbox}- When you have drawn{nl}
 seven cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}- When your total goes{nl}
 over 21 (a bust).{waitkey}{clearbox}Cards 2-10 count as their{nl}
face value,{waitkey}J-K count as 10,{waitkey}and an Ace counts as{nl}
either 1 or 11.{waitkey}{clearbox}After the player STANDs,{nl}
the dealer draws cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}If your total stays under{nl}
21 and beats the dealer's{nl}
total,{waitkey}or if the dealer busts,{nl}
you win.{waitkey}{clearbox}If the dealer and player{nl}
tie, or both have{nl}
a Blackjack,{waitkey}it's a draw and your bet{nl}
coins are returned.{waitkey}{clearbox}Besides HIT and STAND, the{nl}
player can also{waitkey}perform a "D.DOWN"{nl}
and a "SPLIT".{waitkey}{clearbox}   <D.DOWN>{nl}
   (Double Down){waitkey}{clearbox}Only possible when the{nl}
player holds two cards.{waitkey}{clearbox}You double your bet, on the{nl}
condition that you HIT exactly{nl}
one more card.{waitkey}{clearbox}You can't do it if you hold{nl}
fewer coins than the bet.{waitkey}{clearbox}If you Double Down and beat{nl}
the dealer, your payout{nl}
doubles.{waitkey}{clearbox}   <SPLIT>{nl}
   (Split){waitkey}{clearbox}Possible when the player's{nl}
first two cards are the same{nl}
number.{waitkey}{clearbox}You split the two cards into{nl}
two separate hands and play{nl}
them both.{waitkey}{clearbox}You can't do it if you hold{nl}
fewer coins than the bet.{waitkey}{clearbox}Even after a SPLIT, you can{nl}
still D.DOWN on each{nl}
hand.{waitkey}{clearbox}However, after a SPLIT,{nl}
an Ace with a 10-K{nl}
that follows{waitkey}is not a Blackjack and{nl}
counts only as 21.{waitkey}{clearbox}[About INSURANCE]{waitkey}{clearbox}INSURANCE is{nl}
a kind of insurance,{nl}
offered to you{waitkey}only when the dealer's first{nl}
card is an Ace.{waitkey}{clearbox}To take INSURANCE choose{nl}
YES; to decline, choose NO.{waitkey}{clearbox}Choose NO and play{nl}
proceeds as normal.{waitkey}{clearbox}Choose YES and you first{nl}
pay half your bet as the{nl}
premium.{waitkey}Then if the dealer's other{nl}
card is a 10-K,{waitkey}that is, a Blackjack,{nl}
your bet is forfeit,{waitkey}but you get back three times{nl}
the premium, and the{nl}
game ends.{waitkey}{clearbox}And if the dealer's card{nl}
is A-9,{waitkey}the premium is forfeit{nl}
and play proceeds as normal.{waitkey}{clearbox}Note: this game uses{nl}
four decks (208 cards),{nl}
so the same card{waitkey}may come up two or{nl}
more times.{waitkey}{ret}

