On a slot machine, the{nl}
symbols that hit easily{nl}
differ between machines.{waitkey}{clearbox}Rather than stick to one{nl}
machine, it's best to try{nl}
out various machines.{waitkey}{clearbox}Also, it's easy to forget to{nl}
spin the small drums during{nl}
play, so take care.{waitkey}Adjusting the small drums well{nl}
is the secret to growing your{nl}
coins.{waitkey}{clearbox}Note: betting small risks a{nl}
big loss at the crucial{nl}
moment.{waitkey}It's best to always go in at{nl}
8 BET (full bet).{waitkey}{ret}

Two dice are rolled on{nl}
the screen, and you guess{nl}
their total.{waitkey}{clearbox}You can bet on 11 spots,{nl}
2 through 12, as many spots{nl}
per game as you like,{waitkey}up to 100 bet per{nl}
spot.{waitkey}{clearbox}If you bet on the dice total,{nl}
you win and earn a payout{nl}
set by the odds.{waitkey}{clearbox}You can also wager that{nl}
payout to play an Extra Game.{waitkey}{clearbox}In the Extra Game you don't{nl}
"guess the total"{nl}
— instead,{waitkey}"so long as the total isn't 7,{nl}
any total wins"{nl}
is the game.{waitkey}(payouts vary by{nl}
total){waitkey}But if a 7 comes up it's over,{nl}
and that payout is all{nl}
forfeit, so take care.{waitkey}{ret}

