In this game, the closer a{nl}
number is to 7 the lower its{nl}
payout, but the more likely{nl}
it is to hit.{waitkey}{clearbox}So it's safest to bet more on{nl}
numbers near 7 and less on{nl}
numbers near 2 or 12.{waitkey}{clearbox}Also, in the Extra Game, if a{nl}
7 comes up all your won coins{nl}
are forfeit,{waitkey}so the trick to not losing is{nl}
to quit at a sensible point{nl}
without getting greedy.{waitkey}{ret}

In a 3x3 grid of nine{nl}
squares, the numbers 1-9 are{nl}
scattered at random.{waitkey}{clearbox}Guess the arrangement of{nl}
the scattered numbers.{waitkey}{clearbox}The faster you guess,{nl}
the better the prize.{waitkey}{clearbox}If you can't answer within{nl}
the set number of tries,{nl}
it's game over.{waitkey}{clearbox}The set number of tries is{nl}
the count of "RESULT" on{nl}
the right of the screen.{waitkey}{clearbox}"RESULT" is written in turn{nl}
whenever your entered{nl}
answer is wrong,{waitkey}so use it as a guide for{nl}
your next answer.{waitkey}{clearbox}Also, the "CHOSEN" shown{nl}
above the entry spaces{waitkey}lights up when a number is{nl}
selected, dark if not.{waitkey}Check each number's light to{nl}
see whether 1-9 are spread{nl}
out evenly, with no dupes.{waitkey}{clearbox}Note: this game uses{nl}
"Metal Cards," not coins.{waitkey}{ret}

